bilingual.source: The tenant was evicted due to arrears in rent.
bilingual.target: 由于租金欠款，房客被驱逐了。

bilingual.source: The new tenant is occupying the apartment next to mine.
bilingual.target: 新房客占据了我旁边的公寓。
你又是否作个好房客呢？

bilingual.source: The previous tenant just moved out yesterday.
bilingual.target: 上一位房客昨天刚搬走。

bilingual.source: Tenant: I want to report a broken hot water heater.
bilingual.target: 房客: 我想报告热水炉坏了.

bilingual.source: Better an empty house than an ill tenant.
bilingual.target: 宁可让房子空着，不愿招恶房客进住。

bilingual.source: The tenant was dispossessed for not paying his rent.
bilingual.target: 那名房客因未付房租而被赶走。

bilingual.source: The tenant was evicted for non-payment of rent.
bilingual.target: 这个房客因为没有交房租而被赶出去了。

yingyinNormal.en: I don't see why we can't get a new tenant when the Drewes are gone.
yingyinNormal.zh: 德鲁一家搬走了，我觉得可以再找个佃户。

yingyinNormal.en: How is the luncheon for the tenant farmers coming along? Well, I think. Tom?
yingyinNormal.zh: 佃户午餐准备得怎么样了？应该很好吧，汤姆？

yingyinNormal.en: Two to one, you lose. Not so fast. I believe we have one tenant here who has not made her voice heard.
yingyinNormal.zh: 2比1，你输了。别急。我们还有一位租客没有发言呢。

yingyinNormal.en: What? How? There's a tenant farmer, whose family has been at Downton for years. I'm sure he can be trusted.
yingyinNormal.zh: 什么？怎么做？有个佃户，他一家在唐顿生活了多年，我们能信任他。

yingyinNormal.en: Why? What do you mean? It's just, we got another notice about the space in Butte County. We'll find a tenant. It just takes time.
yingyinNormal.zh: 为什么，你这是什么意思？就是，我们又收到催款通知了，布尤特县的那块空地。我们会找到租户的，就是需要时间。

yingyinNormal.en: In 1931, Thomas Edison confided to his friend, Henry Ford, "we are like tenant farmers, chopping down the fence around our house for fuel, when we should be using nature's inexhaustible sources of energy, sun, wind, and tide."
yingyinNormal.zh: 1931年，托马斯·爱迪生悄悄告诉他的朋友亨利·福特"，我们就像土地租用人，当我们需要时，砍我们房子周边的篱笆做燃料，自然就是取之不尽用之不竭的能源，太阳，风和潮水"。
